# How to access EC2 Instance even if PEM file is lost


Step1- Stop the machine and detach the volume 

Step2- launch new ec2 instance through new  pem key and attach old machine ebs volume 
       device name /dev/xvdbp
step3- login through new ec2 instance after you get two ebs volume 
       lsblk
       mount /dev/xvdbp1 /mnt
       cp /root/.ssh/authorized_keys /mnt/root/.ssh/
       umount /mnt
       Detach the old ebs volume 

step4- old ebs volume attach with old machine    /dev/sda1/


